Indicator Name: Population ages 20-24, female (% of female population)
Long definition: Female population between the ages 20 to 24 as a percentage of the total female population.
Source: World Bank staff estimates based on age/sex distributions of United Nations Population Division's World Population Prospects: 2017 Revision.

Indicator Name: Population ages 20-24, male (% of male population)
Long definition: Male population between the ages 20 to 24 as a percentage of the total male population.
Source: World Bank staff estimates based on age/sex distributions of United Nations Population Division's World Population Prospects: 2017 Revision.
